  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Promoting Accountability in Mineral revenue management</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">- Analyse and educate communities on the MDF Act 912
- Development of a Mining revenue toolkit for community sensitization and mobilization through the establishment of Citizens Accountability Team (CAT) Enhancing the capacity of community members of the 3-local government areas on Social Accountability, value for money audits, and analysis of procurement contracts.
- Institutionalizing and internalizing the fight against corruption in mining affected.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Communities are familiar with the MDF and the allocation formula
Quality of spending mineral royalty is improved.
The process of selecting projects funded with mineral royalty is made participatory, fair and transparent.
Citizens in the beneficiary districts are well informed and empowered to demand for accountability regarding the proper utilization of mineral royalties.
Government committed to releases mineral royalties on time to Assemblies while the District authorities committed to properly utilised the funds for the provision of development programmes that will benefit the citizens.
Reduction in opportunities for corruption and enhancement of sanctions regime.</narrative>
  </description>
